# Project Fundamentals

1. Use bun instead of node
2. Use Svelte features where applicable
3. Don't add unprompted new styles or features
4. Break down large tasks into smaller tasks
5. If a better way is available, suggest it but don't assume
6. If you don't know how to do something, ask

# Credit Efficiency

6. Minimize tool calls by combining related searches
7. Prefer direct file edits over multiple view operations
8. Focus questions on specific files or components
9. Use specific line ranges when viewing files
10. Provide complete context in questions to avoid follow-ups

# Code Organization

11. Keep related code changes in single operations
12. Document complex logic inline to reduce future queries
13. Use descriptive variable and function names to improve clarity
14. Maintain a consistent file structure
15. Keep components focused and single-purpose
